Good afternoon David and Chris,

Thank you for your follow-up email, David, and for clarifying the =
misunderstanding from our call. I appreciate your flexibility, and since =
you=E2=80=99re busy on Tuesday, Wednesday at 2:00 PM works for =
me=E2=80=94please confirm if that suits.

Before we proceed, I want to reiterate two key priorities to ensure a =
safe and effective process:

Assessment-Focused Work: Initial tasks should enable damage assessment =
(e.g., securing the site, removing debris for inspection) rather than =
repairs (e.g., cleaning curtains or upholstery), allowing me to exercise =
my right to an independent assessment and for both parties to agree on a =
remediation plan.
Health & Safety (H&S) Risk Mitigation: No work should start until H&S =
risks are identified and addressed by independent experts, given the =
master electrician=E2=80=99s finding that the property is uninhabitable =
due to electrical hazards.


I=E2=80=99ve been told by firefighters that there was substantial fire =
damage and significant smoke exiting the roof=E2=80=94initially thought =
to originate there by Devonport Flagstaff=E2=80=94which penetrated the =
house structure. Yet, the roof, the gas unit beneath it, and overall =
structural integrity remain uninspected.  This, alongside asbestos and =
moisture concerns, raises serious safety issues.

I=E2=80=99m particularly worried about the asbestos plan. The scope =
mentions removing less than 10m=C2=B2, but the deck=E2=80=99s =
fire-damaged section connects to the main area, suggesting potential =
wider involvement. I raised this with Chris, requesting a full =
inspection, and I=E2=80=99d like this addressed before any removal =
begins.

Could we please align on this H&S-first, assessment-only approach? I=E2=80=
=99d prefer to defer repair-focused cleaning until after experts assess =
the damage and we agree on a plan. This seems fair to ensure safety and =
accuracy=E2=80=94do you agree? I=E2=80=99m happy to discuss this onsite =
at 2:00 PM Wednesday if confirmed.

Thanks so much for your understanding=E2=80=94I look forward to your =
response.

Kind regards,
Raffaella del Prete

On 30 Jun 2025, at 11:25=E2=80=AFAM, David Tallot =
