> Subject: Re: 23 Mays street Devenport
> =20
> Hi David,
> =20
> Thank you for your call earlier and for sending the email. I=E2=80=99m =
a bit concerned, as we just spoke over the phone and I explained that I =
cannot meet you on Monday with such short notice (less than 24 working =
hours). You had agreed to send me the scope of work with a few available =
options for when we could meet (not Monday) and that I would get back to =
you.
> =20
> I=E2=80=99m not sure why, just minutes after our call, you=E2=80=99re =
now pressing me to meet at 12 PM despite our agreement to sync back on =
Monday to find a convenient time. This feels a little unexpected.
> =20
> I=E2=80=99m also worried about the sequencing and the Health & Safety =
aspects of the proposed scope, which I=E2=80=99d like to discuss further =
when we arrange a suitable time.
> =20
> Thanks and regards,
> Raffaella del Prete
> =20
> =20
> On 27 Jun 2025, at 2:41=E2=80=AFPM, David Tallot =
<david@assetrestore.co.nz <mailto:david@assetrestore.co.nz>> wrote:
> =20
> Hi Raffaella=20
> =20
> Thanks for your time on the phone earlier.
> =20
> As discussed, Tower insurance has approved our quote to carry out the =
following work we discussed at your house. (Scope attached)
> =20
> Can I please come and meet with you Monday 12pm ? so we can go through =
the scope together and I can show my staff who will be doing the work, =
we can then also arrange key access with you and install a lock box.
> =20
> Thanks
> =20
> =20
> =20
> =20
